You are analyzing one or more scanned images from oceanographic field datasheets related to MOCNESS (Multiple Opening/Closing Net and Environmental Sensing System) tows.

Each tow may have either:
- A single image with all structured metadata and net table
- Or two images: a form page and a second notes page containing handwritten biological or procedural comments

The association between these pages is identified by the file name:

### FILE NAMING CONVENTION:
- tow_<ID>_form.png → the primary structured form page
- tow_<ID>_notes.png → the corresponding handwritten notes page for the same tow

Extract the following as a single JSON object:
- Header metadata (cruise, date, wind, location, lat/long, etc.)
- Net rows with: net number, time, depth, angle, flow, volume, and comments
- Merge any handwritten comments from notes page by matching net number
- Combine duplicate comments with `;` separator
- Format all dates as yyyy-mm-dd
- Ignore rows with neither time nor depth
- Interpret slashed-zero symbols as the number 0